{"id":7631,"date":"2017-10-21T10:05:55","date_gmt":"2017-10-21T10:05:55","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?p=7631"},"modified":"2019-07-12T10:34:04","modified_gmt":"2019-07-12T10:34:04","slug":"trello-vsts-integration","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/10\/21\/trello-vsts-integration\/","title":{"rendered":"Two Backlogs Integration (Trello &#038; VSTS)"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc493934017\">Introduction. <\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc493934018\">Connecting to Trello. <\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc493934019\">Creating automation in Zapier. <\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc493934020\">Example of moving the Trello card between the different states. 9<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc493934017\"><\/a>Introduction<\/h2>\n<p>The idea of having the two backlogs can still be pretty new to many people.\u00a0 So I will first try to explain in this posts the philosophy behind the usage of different backlogs and present the integration of different management systems. The <strong>Operations backlog<\/strong> or <strong>Ops backlog<\/strong> is usually a backlog for management of business and end users. Where incidents, problems, tickets and service requests are being recorded. By monitoring and event management events are dispatched back to the <strong>Development backlog<\/strong> or <strong>Dev Backlog.<\/strong> Where the main goal of the team is to deliver constant structural enhancements. To improve the satisfaction and to prevent and incidents affecting the high quality of performance and functionality for the end user.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>In order to ensure a smooth connection between different backlogs, there are some good solutions on the market for incident management. Such as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.servicenow.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Service Now<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.bmc.com\/it-solutions\/remedy-incident-management.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Remedy<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/trello.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Trello<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.zendesk.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ZenDesk<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.uservoice.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">User Voice<\/a> and much more. To get more insights from real examples, in many of my projects the development. Which is using <strong>Dev Backlog<\/strong> was made in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/dev-essentials\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Visual Studio<\/strong><\/a> and integrated with<strong> Ops Backlogs.<\/strong> Using different incident management apps mentioned above. The idea is well captured in the image below:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/DevOps.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-7659\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/DevOps.png\" alt=\"DevOps\" width=\"954\" height=\"528\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/DevOps.png 954w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/DevOps-300x166.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/DevOps-768x425.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 954px) 100vw, 954px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Further, in this post, I will show the example of how to make the integration between <strong>Trello<\/strong> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/team-services\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>VSTS<\/strong><\/a>, which will enable us to see all changes in the state of work items on the boards of each application. We\u2019ll use Zapier to connect both applications and Zapier will enable us to automate tasks between both apps.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip<\/span>You can find more information about <strong>DevOps<\/strong> in the following post: <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/10\/31\/devops-the-three-stage-conversation-people-process-products\/\">DevOps: The Three Stage Conversation &#8211; People, Process, Products<\/a> which describes the basic principles of <strong>DevOps<\/strong>. This post will be especially helpful to those for whom DevOps is still a new concept. If you prefer a deeper view on this topic, have a look at the following guide: <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/11\/03\/published-a-quick-guide-about-basic-principles-of-devops\/\">quick guide about Basic Principles of DevOps<\/a>, which presents an overview of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/vs\/devops\/\">DevOps <\/a>process and practices, describing \u201cthe big picture\u201d, while still maintaining the high level of detail.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc493934018\"><\/a>Connecting to Trello<\/h2>\n<p>First, we\u2019ll need to log into Trello with a valid account.<\/p>\n<p>1. For our case, we have connected with valid <strong>Google account<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.1-Connecting-to-Trello.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7632\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.1-Connecting-to-Trello-1024x556.png\" alt=\"1.1-Connecting to Trello\" width=\"760\" height=\"413\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.1-Connecting-to-Trello-1024x556.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.1-Connecting-to-Trello-300x163.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.1-Connecting-to-Trello-768x417.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.1-Connecting-to-Trello.jpg 1141w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>2. After we <strong>log into Trello<\/strong>, we\u2019ll be able to see all the teams that we can join.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.2-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7633\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.2-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards-1024x483.png\" alt=\"1.2-Connecting to Trello_Boards\" width=\"760\" height=\"358\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.2-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards-1024x483.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.2-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards-300x142.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.2-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards-768x363.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.2-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards.png 1129w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>3. With clicking on the <strong>team\u2019s board Icon<\/strong> we\u2019ll be able to join the team for which we want to create automation on <strong>Zapier<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.3-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards_settings-1.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7636\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.3-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards_settings-1-1024x496.png\" alt=\"1.3-Connecting to Trello_Boards_settings\" width=\"760\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.3-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards_settings-1-1024x496.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.3-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards_settings-1-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.3-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards_settings-1-768x372.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.3-Connecting-to-Trello_Boards_settings-1.png 1129w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>4. With opening <strong>the board of the team in Trello<\/strong>, we see all the boards of the team. Here we can add a new board. Change the colors of the current boards or any other settings of the board. Such as team members for example.the colors of the current boards or any other settings of the board, such as team members for example.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.4-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_settings-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7637\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.4-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_settings-1-1024x497.png\" alt=\"1.4-Connecting to Trello_Board_settings\" width=\"760\" height=\"369\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.4-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_settings-1-1024x497.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.4-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_settings-1-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.4-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_settings-1-768x372.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.4-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_settings-1.jpg 1128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>5. With choosing the <strong>team\u2019s board<\/strong>, a new window will appear with the board settings. On the right side of the side window, we will have the board\u2019s settings. Where we will be able to see the activity of the team, with all team members. We\u2019ll be able also to see the <strong>Join the team button<\/strong>, which we need to choose in order to create an integration in later steps.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.5-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_joining-the-team.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7638\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.5-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_joining-the-team-1024x499.png\" alt=\"1.5-Connecting to Trello_Board_joining the team\" width=\"760\" height=\"370\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.5-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_joining-the-team-1024x499.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.5-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_joining-the-team-300x146.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.5-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_joining-the-team-768x374.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/1.5-Connecting-to-Trello_Board_joining-the-team.png 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">More Info<\/span>If you want to know more about maintaining the backlog in a proper way, you can visit the following post: <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/11\/30\/key-tips-for-maintaining-good-product-backlog-in-agile-and-scrum\/\">Key Tips For Maintaining Good Product Backlog in Agile and Scrum<\/a>. The post describes a way to efficiently organize the <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-us\/vsts\/work\/backlogs\/create-your-backlog\">backlog<\/a> items allowing you to understand the requirements better, and providing you with higher level of detail of what is actually expected from the work or delivery perspective.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc493934019\"><\/a>Creating automation in Zapier<\/h2>\n<p>In your <strong>Zapier account<\/strong>, you will need to create a <strong>Zap<\/strong>, which is representing the integration between the apps. On the left side, you will add the triggers and on the right side, you will add the actions.<\/p>\n<p>In the first <strong>Zap<\/strong> on the example below \u2013 Trello-&#8230; to VSTS, we can see that the trigger is set to be <strong>Trello<\/strong> and the action will be done in <strong>VSTS<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7639\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x527.png\" alt=\"2-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"391\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x527.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x154.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x395.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1127w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>On the example below, you will be able to see the <strong>integration or the Zap for Trello<\/strong> &#8230; cards to VSTS.<\/p>\n<p>1. With clicking on the arrow on the right side of the <strong>Zap<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>2. You will be able to choose from the drop-down menu the<strong> Edit option<\/strong>, to see or edit the settings of this integration.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.1-Creating-automation-in-Zapier_Zap.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7640\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.1-Creating-automation-in-Zapier_Zap-1024x494.png\" alt=\"2.1-Creating automation in Zapier_Zap\" width=\"760\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.1-Creating-automation-in-Zapier_Zap-1024x494.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.1-Creating-automation-in-Zapier_Zap-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.1-Creating-automation-in-Zapier_Zap-768x371.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.1-Creating-automation-in-Zapier_Zap.png 1127w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>In this integration, we\u2019ve set 3 steps, but please note that the step 2 is not really used and it\u2019s unnecessary as it doesn\u2019t provide any function. You will be able to see it, in order to just get an idea that we can use also different filters as the steps.<\/p>\n<p>3. In the<strong> Connection to the Trello<\/strong>, where we have set different options for connection and in the first part we first chose the app for our connection, which is <strong>Trello<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.3-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7641\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.3-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x507.png\" alt=\"2.3-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"376\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.3-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x507.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.3-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x149.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.3-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x381.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.3-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1126w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>4. Then we define the <strong>Trello trigger<\/strong>, which is in our case when the <strong>Trello card is moved to the list.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.4-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7642\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.4-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x495.png\" alt=\"2.4-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.4-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x495.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.4-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.4-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x371.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.4-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1123w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>5. After that, we have defined the account with which we are connected to Trello, where is a good idea to<strong> test if the connection to the account is working fine<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.5-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7643\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.5-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png\" alt=\"2.5-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.5-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.5-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.5-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x370.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.5-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>6. Next, we&#8217;ll move to\u00a0<strong>Edit Options<\/strong>, where we chose the <strong>Trello board<\/strong> for which we want to have the integration, the list of the stage for which we want to set the trigger and the type of the card that we want to use.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.6-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7644\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.6-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x496.png\" alt=\"2.6-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.6-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x496.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.6-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.6-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x372.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.6-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1126w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>7. Once when we finish with the settings of the step, we need to <strong>test it<\/strong> in order to be able to move to the next settings of our integration.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.7-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7645\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.7-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x492.png\" alt=\"2.7-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"365\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.7-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x492.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.7-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x144.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.7-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x369.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.7-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>8. We can set also the <strong>filters<\/strong>, where we set the triggers to be working only in the case where the card name doesn\u2019t already exist so that we are able to avoid any duplication of the work items. But as explained before, this filter is not really needed for this zap as it will not do anything.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.8-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7646\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.8-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x495.png\" alt=\"2.8-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.8-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x495.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.8-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.8-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x371.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.8-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1124w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>9. In the <strong>Connection to VSTS backlog<\/strong>, we will choose the action, which will appear in the <strong>VSTS backlog<\/strong>. So, first, we will <strong>connect our VSTS account<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.9-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7647\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.9-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png\" alt=\"2.9-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.9-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.9-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x144.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.9-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x370.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.9-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1126w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>10. Then we will choose the option, in which the <strong>new work item will be created<\/strong> based on the trigger from the first step.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.10-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7648\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.10-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png\" alt=\"2.10-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.10-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.10-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x144.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.10-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x370.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.10-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1126w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>11. We\u2019ve chosen the account with which we are connecting to our <strong>VSTS backlog<\/strong> and again, before continuing to the next step of setting the integration, we need to test if the account connection if working fine.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.11-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7649\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.11-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png\" alt=\"2.11-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.11-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x493.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.11-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x144.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.11-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x370.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.11-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>12. We\u2019ve edited the template, where we chose the VSTS project, the type of the <strong>Work item<\/strong> which will be created and the <strong>Title of the new work item<\/strong>, which will be in our case equal to the <strong>Trello card name<\/strong>. In next options, we chose the <strong>area<\/strong> and the <strong>description<\/strong> of the newly created work item, which will be the same as the <strong>Trello card description<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.12-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7650\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.12-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x495.png\" alt=\"2.12-Creating automation in Zapier\" width=\"760\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.12-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-1024x495.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.12-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.12-Creating-automation-in-Zapier-768x371.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/2.12-Creating-automation-in-Zapier.png 1128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>When we\u2019ve set all the requirements for our integration, we need to test the settings, by going through the process.<\/p>\n<p>You will see that we have created in our Zapier account three more integrations or zap\u2019s for automation of different state changes. The same idea or philosophy was used also in this zaps. Where of course we first connected both accounts and chose the appropriate steps. Such as the filters which will tell us when to continue to the next step and for which state changes we want to see the automation.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip<\/span> The post <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/09\/18\/user-stories-in-agile-world\/\">User stories in Agile world <\/a> focuses on an important unit of Agile software development process. Which is <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-us\/vsts\/work\/work-items\/guidance\/agile-process-workflow\">User Story<\/a>. The post also describes some basic rules and recommendations you have to follow before adding the descriptions of <strong>PBI<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc493934020\"><\/a>Example of moving the Trello card between the different states<\/h2>\n<p>For this example, we created a <strong>test card in Trello<\/strong>, which is not visible yet in the <strong>VSTS backlog<\/strong>. Considering the rules and filters that we previously set in the Zapier. When we move the card from the state Suggestions\/Ideas to the Suggested Ideas \u2013 Added to TFS. We\u2019ll see that the card will appear as a work item in our VSTS backlog.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.1-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7651\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.1-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x481.png\" alt=\"3.1-Example of moving the Trello card between the different states\" width=\"760\" height=\"357\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.1-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x481.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.1-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-300x141.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.1-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-768x360.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.1-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png 1127w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>As we set in our Zap that the trigger will run every five minutes. The work item will appear in our VSTS backlog after this five minutes. Of course, if we want to see it immediately. We can navigate to the Zapier, choose our Zap and manually set the trigger to run immediately.<\/p>\n<p>We\u2019ll see the<strong> new work item in the bottom of our backlog<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.2-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7652\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.2-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x496.png\" alt=\"3.2-Example of moving the Trello card between the different states\" width=\"760\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.2-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x496.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.2-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.2-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-768x372.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.2-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png 1129w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>When we add our new work item in the current sprint and move it to the <strong>Committed state<\/strong>. We\u2019ll be instantly able to see this change appear on the <strong>Trello board<\/strong>. In the image below you will see that we moved our <strong>Test Work item<\/strong> in the <strong>Committed state<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.3-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7653\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.3-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x499.png\" alt=\"3.3-Example of moving the Trello card between the different states\" width=\"760\" height=\"370\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.3-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x499.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.3-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-300x146.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.3-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-768x374.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.3-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png 1125w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>And we will be instantly able to see this change in our Trello board.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.4-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-7654\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.4-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x495.png\" alt=\"3.4-Example of moving the Trello card between the different states\" width=\"760\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.4-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-1024x495.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.4-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-300x145.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.4-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states-768x371.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/09\/3.4-Example-of-moving-the-Trello-card-between-the-different-states.png 1127w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Remember, this will happen due to our previous settings in the Zapier. Where we mapped the Committed state from VSTS backlog with the Working on the state on the Trello.<\/p>\n<p>For example, if we try to move the work item in the VSTS backlog to the Groomed state. Nothing will happen on the Trello board. As the Groomed state of VSTS backlog is not mapped to any state of the Trello board.<\/p>\n<p>The same automation will happen when we move the work item of our VSTS backlog to the state Done. As the VSTS backlog state Done is mapped to the Deployed state of our Trello board. Again, this automation is done, based on the settings that we chose previously in our Zap.<\/p>\n<p>The same automation between the work items and the Trello card can be done for any other state. Such as Awaiting Deployment or Testing, we just need to set it in our Zap\u2019s.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">More Info<\/span>Read detailed explanation about all types of <strong>Scrum and Agile meetings<\/strong> (Sprint Planning, Stand-up, Grooming, <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-us\/vsts\/work\/scrum\/sprint-planning\">Sprint<\/a> Review, Retrospective Meeting) in my past post <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/11\/27\/types-of-meetings-in-scrum-and-agile\/\">Types of meetings in Scrum and Agile<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>&nbsp; Introduction. Connecting to Trello. Creating automation in Zapier. Example &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"ast-button\" href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2017\/10\/21\/trello-vsts-integration\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Two Backlogs Integration (Trello &#038; VSTS)<\/span> Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":7657,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[15,837,16,23,834],"tags":[70,205],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/7631"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=7631"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/7631\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":9471,"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/7631\/revisions\/9471"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/